🎓 EduTech – A Simple Educational Website Landing Page
Hi there! 👋
Welcome to EduTech, a clean, responsive, and beginner-friendly educational landing page built using just HTML and CSS. It’s perfect for showcasing an online learning platform, coaching center, or any education-based service.

✨ What’s Inside?
This website includes:

✅ A modern navigation bar with a logo and links

🎯 A colorful and eye-catching hero section with a CTA (Call to Action)

📚 A Features section to highlight what the platform offers

🧑‍🏫 An About Us section with a quick overview of the team or mission

📞 A Contact section to get in touch

🔐 A simple and clean Login Form

🌐 A neat Footer with social media links

All wrapped up in a smooth, animated, and mobile-responsive design.

🧱 Project Structure
Here's how everything is organized:

css
Copy
Edit
📁 EduTech/
├── index.html        → Main webpage
├── style.css         → CSS styling file
└── edulogo.avif      → Logo image (used in navbar)
🛠 Tech Used
HTML5 – to structure the web page

CSS3 – for styling and responsiveness

AVIF Image Format – for the logo (modern and lightweight)

🚀 Getting Started
To run the project on your system:

Download or clone the repo.

Make sure index.html, style.css, and edulogo.avif are all in the same folder.

Open index.html with any browser (Chrome, Firefox, Edge, etc.).

Boom 💥 — You’ve got your landing page live locally!

✅ Tip: If your browser doesn’t show the logo (edulogo.avif), try converting it to .png or .jpg and update the <img src="..."> path.

